08 May 2022

Introduction

The study

It is known that the use of broad-spectrum antibiotics can promote the spread of resistant strains by competition. A previous study by Letten, A.D., Baumgartner, M., Pfrunder-Cardozo, K.R. et al. (2021) analysed the competitive suppression of a resistant strain of E. coli inoculated into human gut-microbiota populations within the presence and absence of rifampicin and polymyxin B.

Materials and methods

Data extracted from Letten, A.D., Baumgartner, M., Pfrunder-Cardozo, K.R. et al.(2021).
